Let A be a $m \times d$ complex random matrix, distributed according to Haar
  measure on the unitary group U(m) of complex Hermitian matrices of dimension m. Let $\sigma_i(A)$ denote the $i$-th singular value of A. Haar measure on U(m) is of the form
\begin{align*}
 P(U) dU = const. \prod_{i=1}^{i=min(m,d)} \frac{1}{D_i+1} vol(SO(D_i)) du_{\mathfrak{u}(D_i)},
\end{align*}
where $U$ denotes the unitary matrix, $vol(SO(D_i))$ denotes the volume of SO(D$_i$), and $du_{\mathfrak{u}(D_i)}$ denotes
the invariant Haar measure on $\mathfrak{u}(m)$, where dim($U(m)$)=dim($U(d)$) holds.

By considering a unitary matrix U with dimension $maxe(d,m)$, we get
\begin{align*}
\int_{U(m)} \sigma_i(A) dU &= \frac{1}{\sqrt{d-i + 1}} \Sigma_{j=1}^{d-i + 1} \int_{U(m)} \sigma_j(A \Sigma^{-1}) dU
\end{align*}
holds.
\end{abstract}


