   year={1988},

In this paper, we aim to provide a novel and efficient algorithm for efficient image segmentation. We propose a novel method of using a temporal convolutional network to create a deep low-dimensional representation of the image with a set of global parameters and a large number of local parameters. In the presented method we use a temporal convolutional network to apply exponential softmax over each image pixel and minimize the sum of non-linear costs for images with an appropriate number of features and a non-zero feature vector. We propose a fast, efficient and scalable implementation of this model in the cuDNN framework. We apply these models to an image segmentation task and show it is superior to other existing algorithms for such task including convolution networks, Gaussian networks, and SGD. We believe the results can be useful for image segmentation in practice and application.

